    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="39"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d39">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Marshal <persName corresp="#p_SIV1" type="from"
                            >Stalin</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d39fn1">Apparently sent via the Soviet Embassy, Washington.
                        The entire document is printed in <hi rend="italic">
                            <persName corresp="#p_SIV1">Stalin</persName>’s Correspondence</hi>,
                        vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 97.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-06">October 6,
                            1943</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">Translation</p>
                <p>Personal and secret from Premier <persName corresp="#p_SIV1">J. V.
                        Stalin</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Franklin D.
                        Roosevelt</persName>.</p>
                <p>I received your message of October 4th.<note n="2" xml:id="d39fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_27">p. 27</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Our representatives<note n="3" xml:id="d39fn3">At the forthcoming Moscow
                        Conference of Foreign Ministers.</note> have to do everything possible to
                    prevent possible difficulties in their responsible work. It is understood that
                    the decisions as such can be made only by our governments and I hope they will
                    be made at my personal meeting with you and Mr. <persName corresp="#p_CC2"
                        >Churchill</persName>.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">October</hi> 6, 1943.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
